/*
================= GOLDEN RULES OF RUNTIME POLYMORPHISM =================

Rule 1:
Compiler hamesha Reference Type (left side) ko dekhta hai aur wahi decide karta hai
ki kaun se methods call karne ki permission hai.

Rule 2:
JVM (Runtime) hamesha Actual Object (right side) ko dekhta hai aur agar method
override hua hai to Actual Object ka method call karta hai.

Rule 3:
Agar method override nahi hua hai, to Parent (Reference Type) ka inherited method
hi execute hota hai.

=======================================================================
*/